# 3-Class Baseline (Dysfunctional)
# Purpose: Poorly wired network to test evaluation vs crafted 3-class network.
# Characteristics:
# - Direct S->O mapping for all classes with equal strength.
# - No inhibitory pool neuron.
# - Expect ambiguous winners under noise and poor separation.

# NEURON <id> <threshold> <leak> <resting>
# CONNECTION <from_id> <to_id> <weight>

# Sensory
NEURON S0 100.0 1.0 0.0
NEURON S1 100.0 1.0 0.0
NEURON S2 100.0 1.0 0.0

# Outputs (no inhibitory pool)
NEURON O0 50.0 1.0 0.0
NEURON O1 50.0 1.0 0.0
NEURON O2 50.0 1.0 0.0

# Equal feedforward from all S* to all O* (intentionally wrong)
CONNECTION S0 O0 60.0
CONNECTION S0 O1 60.0
CONNECTION S0 O2 60.0

CONNECTION S1 O0 60.0
CONNECTION S1 O1 60.0
CONNECTION S1 O2 60.0

CONNECTION S2 O0 60.0
CONNECTION S2 O1 60.0
CONNECTION S2 O2 60.0

# Mutual inhibition (winner-take-all)
CONNECTION O0 O1 -8.0
CONNECTION O1 O0 -8.0
CONNECTION O0 O2 -8.0
CONNECTION O2 O0 -8.0
CONNECTION O1 O2 -8.0
CONNECTION O2 O1 -8.0
